==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Soybean
<hw>Soy"bean</hw> <pr>(soi"b⟦emac⟧n`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>An Asiatic leguminous herb (<spn>Glycine
max</spn>, formerly <spn>Glycine Soja</spn>) the seeds of which (also
called <prod>soy beans</prod>) are used in preparing the sauce called
<prod>soy</prod>. Called also <altname>soya bean</altname> and
<altname>soya</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>the seeds of the <spn>Glycine max</spn>, which
produce <er>soybean oil</er>; -- called also <altname>soya
bean</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Soybean oil</ent>⟦br⟧
